    <item>
      <title>3rd Annual Solutions to Heal and Restore the Soul of our Community Conference at Howard University School of Social Work</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/53065132089986/huge/20aad80b7b0b327fa05e4b9e2870ba7826d19096.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Sat, 13 Jun 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>Join us for the 3rd Annual Solutions to Heal and Restore the Soul of Our Community Conference</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Date: Saturday, June 13, 2026
<br>Location: Howard University School of Social Work
<br>Hosted by: Howard University Multidisciplinary Gerontology Center (HU MGC) and Community Partners</p>

<p> </p>

<p>This year's conference will focus on:</p>

<p>• Healing and restoring community connections
<br>• Fatherhood and family engagement
<br>• Intergenerational relationships and social connection
<br>• Health and wellness education
<br>• Aging in place and reducing social isolation
<br>• Community-based solutions for stronger families and neighborhoods
<br>• Arts, culture, storytelling, and restorative practices</p>

<p> </p>

<p>We are especially excited to feature Dr Frank Malone of 100 Fathers Inc.  and our luncheon presentation by Dr. Dameon “Dr. Dae” Jones of HealthyDaes, along with community leaders, researchers, advocates, and partners working to improve health and well-being across generations.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Whether you are a senior, caregiver, student, parent, grandparent, community advocate, nonprofit leader, or simply someone who cares about the future of our communities, this conference is for you.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Registration: <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/1990144105593?aff=oddtdtcreator">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/1990144105593?aff=oddtdtcreator</a></p>

<p><a href="https://events.howard.edu/event/3rd-annual-solutions-to-heal-and-restore-the-soyl-of-our-community-conference">View on site</a> | <a href="mailto:?subject=I found an interesting event%3A 3rd Annual Solutions to Heal and Restore the Soul of our Community Conference&amp;body=I found an interesting event you may like%3A%0A%0A%0ADate%3A Jun 13%2C 2026%0A%0ADescription%3A%0AJoin us for the 3rd Annual Solutions to Heal and Restore the Soul of Our Community Conference%0A%0A %0A%0ADate%3A Saturday%2C June 13%2C 2026%0ALocation%3A Howard University School of Social Work%0AHosted by%3A Howard University Multidisciplinary Gerontology Center %28HU MGC%29 and Community Partners%0A%0A %0A%0AThis year%27s conference will focus on%3A%0A%0A%E2%80%A2 Healing and restoring community connections%0A%E2%80%A2 Fatherhood and family engagement%0A%E2%80%A2 Intergenerational relationships and social connection%0A%E2%80%A2 Health and wellness education%0A%E2%80%A2 Aging in place and reducing social isolation%0A%E2%80%A2 Community-based solutions for stronger families and neighborhoods%0A%E2%80%A2 Arts%2C culture%2C storytelling%2C and restorative practices%0A%0A %0A%0AWe are especially excited to feature Dr Frank Malone of 100 Fathers Inc.  and our luncheon presentation by Dr. Dameon %E2%80%9CDr. Dae%E2%80%9D Jones of HealthyDaes%2C along with community leaders%2C researchers%2C advocates%2C and partners working to improve health and well-being across generations.%0A%0A %0A%0AWhether you are a senior%2C caregiver%2C student%2C parent%2C grandparent%2C community advocate%2C nonprofit leader%2C or simply someone who cares about the future of our communities%2C this conference is for you.%0A%0A %0A%0ARegistration%3A https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eventbrite.com%2Fe%2F1990144105593%3Faff%3Doddtdtcreator%0A%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fevents.howard.edu%2Fevent%2F3rd-annual-solutions-to-heal-and-restore-the-soyl-of-our-community-conference%0A">Email this event</a></p></div></div>]]></description>
