      <title>12th World Sickle Cell Day Symposium -  Is 50 the New 20? Boldly Living Your Best Life with Sickle Cell Disease at Howard University Hospital</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/53071655729871/huge/b98d37c4deabb1d14b2f18122b4a67101bd1f8c6.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Thu, 18 Jun 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>Join the Center for Sickle Cell Disease for an in-person symposium focused on the opportunities and challenges that warriors face as they enter their golden years. Through engaging presentations, expert speakers, and meaningful discussions, attendees will gain valuable insights into healthy aging, wellness, and quality of life. The program will conclude with lunch and guided tours of the new HU Sickle Cell Wellness Center.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>We encourage participants to attend in person to fully experience the event and connect with fellow warriors, caregivers, and community members. A virtual webinar option will also be available for those who cannot join us on site.</p>

<p><a href="https://events.howard.edu/event/12th-world-sickle-cell-day-symposium-is-50-the-new-20-boldly-living-your-best-life-with-sickle-cell-disease">View on site</a> | <a href="mailto:?subject=I found an interesting event%3A 12th World Sickle Cell Day Symposium -  Is 50 the New 20%3F Boldly Living Your Best Life with Sickle Cell Disease&amp;body=I found an interesting event you may like%3A%0A%0A%0ADate%3A Jun 18%2C 2026%0A%0ADescription%3A%0AJoin the Center for Sickle Cell Disease for an in-person symposium focused on the opportunities and challenges that warriors face as they enter their golden years. Through engaging presentations%2C expert speakers%2C and meaningful discussions%2C attendees will gain valuable insights into healthy aging%2C wellness%2C and quality of life. The program will conclude with lunch and guided tours of the new HU Sickle Cell Wellness Center.%0A%0A %0A%0AWe encourage participants to attend in person to fully experience the event and connect with fellow warriors%2C caregivers%2C and community members. A virtual webinar option will also be available for those who cannot join us on site.%0A%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fevents.howard.edu%2Fevent%2F12th-world-sickle-cell-day-symposium-is-50-the-new-20-boldly-living-your-best-life-with-sickle-cell-disease%0A">Email this event</a></p></div></div>]]></description>
